      "title": "Grey Matters Takes Delivery of the First Brain Dedicated PET Scanning System for its Flagship NovaScan Neuroimaging Clinic in Florida",
      "summary": "Grey Matters Health Inc. has received its first brain-dedicated PET scanning system (CareMiBrain) for its flagship NovaScan Neuroimaging Clinic in Davie, Florida, positioning itself as the first U.S. clinic to offer brain-only PET scans for early Alzheimer's detection. The clinic will capitalize on the emerging billion-dollar market created by FDA-approved monoclonal antibody treatments (Leqembi and Kisunla) that require beta-amyloid brain imaging for patient authorization and monitoring.",
